The paper deals with error control in communication channels and storage systems, which are typical topics in information theory (cs.IT). The use of multisets and permutations suggests that the paper may also belong to the categories of discrete structures (cs.DS) and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The construction of error-correcting codes is a central theme in coding theory (cs.CC), and the paper's focus on specific constructions and bounds on code size further supports this category. Finally, the use of specific mathematical concepts such as Sidon sets suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-category of signal processing (cs.SI).
